<taxonomicName id="4C7FCFB7FFB6A35FFE991222FE38AFC4" authority="Bellan-Santini &amp; Dauvin, 2008" authorityName="Bellan-Santini &amp; Dauvin" authorityYear="2008" box="[290,497,1901,1924]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haloops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antarctica" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B90B6826FFB6A35FFE991222FE38AFC4" box="[290,497,1901,1924]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">Haloops antarctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B90B6826FFB6A35FFE441222FDF5AFC5" bold="true" box="[511,572,1901,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A238D55DFFB6A35FFE441222FDF5AFC5" box="[511,572,1901,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="28" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype female, 10mm (ANDEEP III, EBS 154-9). (1) habitus; (2) antenna 1; (3) antenna 2; (4) gnathopod 1; (5) coxal plate 1; (6) gnathopod 2; (7) pereopod 3; (8) pereopod 4; (9) pereopod 5; (10) pereopod 6; (11) pereopod 7; (12) uropod 1; (13) uropod 2; (14) uropod 3; (15) detail of rami of uropod 3; (16) telson. Scale bars: 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF00E4BCFFB7A35EFF2C1617FC98ABD3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5241591" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5241591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5241591/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="29" startId="3.[151,255,856,880]" targetBox="[171,1413,184,828]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BC0B434FFB7A35EFF2C1617FC98ABD3" blockId="3.[151,1435,856,915]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B90B6826FFB7A35EFF2C1617FED3AB30" bold="true" box="[151,282,856,880]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7FCFB7FFB7A35EFE991617FE39AB2F" authority="Bellan-Santini &amp; Dauvin, 2008" authorityName="Bellan-Santini &amp; Dauvin" authorityYear="2008" box="[290,496,856,879]" class="Malacostraca" family="Ampeliscidae" genus="Haloops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antarctica" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B90B6826FFB7A35EFE991617FE39AB2F" box="[290,496,856,879]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">Haloops antarctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B90B6826FFB7A35EFE451617FDF2AB30" bold="true" box="[510,571,856,880]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A238D55DFFB7A35EFE451617FDF2AB30" box="[510,571,856,880]" pageId="3" pageNumber="29" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype female, 10mm (ANDEEP III, EBS 154-9). (1) maxilliped; (2) mandible; (3) maxilla 1; (4) maxilla 2; (5) labium. Scale bars: 100 µm.
</paragraph>
